      "description": "A White Card is the medical benefits identification card issued under the Energy Employees Occupational Illness Compensation Program Act (EEOICPA) that allows approved Department of Energy and Nevada Test Site workers to receive covered medical care — including home health — at no out-of-pocket cost.",
